  "body": "\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: Send tx with Gas price set to 0.0000000023 Gwei (2.3 wei) and get Failed transaction with error message\r\n``` \r\njson: cannot unmarshal invalid hex string into Go struct field SendTxArgs.gasPrice ...\r\n```\r\n![screenshot_20180822-112813](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/44457350-40f96900-a603-11e8-8731-8cb81999969c.png)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nValidate value in gas price field, do not allow to specify invalid number. imo, if we expect only whole 1 gwei or more then we should not allow decimals for wei value, e.g. can set 1 or 2 wei, can't set 1.2 or 2.3 wei in gas price\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nCan set gas price to  0.0000000023 Gwei (2.3 wei) and proceed to sending such tx\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status -> Wallet -> Send transaction -> Advanced\r\n- In Gas price set  0.0000000023 Gwei (2.3 wei)\r\n- Select recipient and set amount to some valid number, e.g. 0.00001 ETH\r\n- Send transaction\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: nightly Aug 21 build\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\nfrom 00:34 https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8564964/sessions/4399086199/?accessToken=GZx0qcekmoMHPfMuey6Iy4SuZO0\r\n[geth.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2309845/geth.log)\r\n\n\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8564964/sessions/4399086199/?accessToken=GZx0qcekmoMHPfMuey6Iy4SuZO0\">TestFairy: Status 0.9.26 (6476) @2018</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
